Program: Omnibus
Title: Civil Aviation
Link: https://www.bbc.co.uk/programmes/p0376jjk
Last Broadcast Date: 12 September 1988
At Farnborough Airshow 1988 with exhibitions including MIG 29 Russian aircraft. The airshow's director Dan Honley explains the importance of the international trade airshow and the significance of seeing Russian pilots shaking hands with British Royal Airforce pilots.